HEADWORD: Unstitch
<hw>Un*stitch"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>stitch</ets>.]</ety> <def>To open by picking out
stitches; to take out, or undo, the stitches of; <as>as, to
<ex>unstitch</ex> a seam</as>.</def> <rj><au>Collier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

